						               													<description>&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;        UNAUTHORIZED PRODUCTION&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;         The information that BGG has on this item indicates that San Guo Sha is an unauthorized reproduction of BANG! with just a few differences, published in China and distributed in several coutries of the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scattered artifacts of the Legends of the Three Kingdoms lay hidden in Cao Cao's tomb.  Find and reassemble the artifact fragments to unlock the power stored within for a millennium!  &amp;#10;What secret is hidden in the tomb?  Who can master the hidden power in the artifacts?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After Cao Cao's tomb was discovered, the explorers delve into the tomb to unlock Cao Cao's secret .  The players will look for artifacts in the tomb through exploration of the debris, excavation or exchange with other explorers.  The artifacts wield special power, and will aid in further exploration of the tomb.  The first player to complete five artifacts wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Though this takes place in the San Guo Sha game setting, this is a stand-alone game of drawing tiles.  Treasure and junk tiles will be placed face down in the middle of the table.  Players will draw two tiles, and keep one.  Then players will trade one of their own face-down tiles with the face-down tile of another player.  The object is to be the first to collect the right tiles that will assemble the lost treasures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comes with:&amp;#10;   60 artifact tiles&amp;#10;   4 character tiles&amp;#10;   1 drawstring bag&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
